comments: Irving (DAL) initiates contact with Conley's (MIN) body, which affects Conley's SQBR on the perimeter.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Irving's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact during the pick.
Referees triggered a review of the goaltending call on Towns (MIN), and the Replay Center confirmed that Towns first touched the ball while was already in the cylinder above the rim.
Doncic (DAL) gathers the pass on his left foot and takes three steps before starting his dribble.
McDaniels (MIN) immediately slides his hand off Lively II's (DAL) side and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Lively II (DAL) lifts his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in Irving's (DAL) path and slightly turns, attempting to brace himself to absorb the ensuing marginal contact as the two come together during the pick.
Doncic (DAL) makes clean contact with the ball and deflects the pass away from Gobert (MIN).
McDaniels (MIN) extends his arm toward the ball when marginal contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) arm as he continues his dribble on the perimeter.
Doncic (DAL) stops his forward momentum and releases from the marginal contact with McDaniels (MIN) at the end of the drive.
Conley (MIN) slightly extends his hips when establishing a screening position and marginal contact occurs with Washington (DAL) as Washington moves over the screen to contest the shot.
McDaniels' (MIN) hand slides off the ball and avoids any illegal contact with Doncic (DAL) during the rebound.
Edwards (MIN) brings his arm toward Irving's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as Irving crosses midcourt.
During the inbound, Jones Jr. (DAL) and Edwards (MIN) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Edwards (MIN) commits a backcourt violation as he receives the pass from the frontcourt before establishing a positive frontcourt position.
Jones Jr. (DAL) legally contests Towns' (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Washington (DAL) attempts to secure the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Reid's (MIN) arm after the release of the put-back shot attempt.
Reid (MIN) commits a take foul on Irving (DAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Washington (DAL) is established in Edwards' (MIN) path and absorbs the marginal body contact as they come together on the way up the court.

Green (DAL) makes contact with Conley's (MIN) arm during his upward shooting motion, which affects his jump shot attempt. The replay center determined the on-court ruling of a three-point field goal attempt would stand.
Lively II (DAL) and Towns (MIN) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs before Towns makes contact with the ball in an attempt to deflect the rebound away from Doncic (DAL).
Gobert (MIN) makes hand-on-ball contact to dislodge the rebound from Doncic (DAL).
